ZCZC OE55
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 142300 UTC
LOW PRESSURE WILL COVER MOST OF THE BRITISH ISLES AND
SURROUNDING WATERS ON WEDNESDAY EVENING WITH THE MAIN
CENTRE OF THE LOW 981 OVER CENTRAL PARTS OF ENGLAND.
DURING THURSDAY THE LOW CENTRE IS EXP TO MOV NE INTO THE
NERN N SEA 981 AND THEN AWAY NE INTO SCANDINAVIA DURING
FRIDAY. LATER ON FRIDAY AND DURING SATURDAY A RIDGE OF
HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO BUILD FM THE W ACROSS THE BRITISH
ISLES. STRG MAINLY N TO NW WINDS ARE EXP TO AFFECT MOST
AREAS ON WEDNESDAY EVENING AND DURING THURSDAY AND AT
FIRST ON FRIDAY WITH A RISK OF GALES IN FAIR ISLE FOR A
TIME ON THURSDAY. WINDS ARE EXP TO EASE ACROSS ALL AREAS
FM THE W DURING FRIDAY. STRG S WINDS ARE EXP TO DEVELOP
IN SHANNON ROCKALL BAILEY AND S-E ICELAND DURING
SATURDAY
